.TH "ib_device_get_by_name" 9 "ib_device_get_by_name" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ib_device_get_by_name \- Find an IB device by name
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct ib_device *" ib_device_get_by_name
.BI "(const char *name "  ","
.BI "enum rdma_driver_id driver_id "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "name" 12
The name to look for
.IP "driver_id" 12
The driver ID that must match (RDMA_DRIVER_UNKNOWN matches all)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Find and hold an ib_device by its name. The caller must call
\fBib_device_put\fP on the returned pointer.
